prompt:
Add a function called ProcessAndLog to Effects.calr that reads from a file, processes the content, and writes to console. The function should properly declare all required effects.

Create this function with proper effect declarations:
§F{f001:ProcessAndLog:pub}
  §I{str:path}
  §O{void}
  §E{fs:r,cw}
  §B{content} §C{File.ReadAllText}
    §A path
  §/C
  §C{Console.WriteLine}
    §A content
  §/C
§/F{f001}

Key point: The function uses both file read (fs:r) and console write (cw) effects, so both must be declared in §E{fs:r,cw}. Calor's effect system enforces this.
